# OOUX Agent Skills — Overview

You have access to OOUX Agent Skills that follow the ORCA (Objects, Relationships, CTAs, Attributes) process — a 3-round, 12-step framework from the X-Ray UX approach (Sophia Prater). All skills live in `.cursor/skills/` (or `~/.claude/skills/`).

**Critical rule:** If data is missing or unclear, always stop and ask the user. Never guess, invent, or use placeholder data. See the `ooux-collaboration` rule for details.

## The Four Ancient Truths of OOUX

These truths — rooted in human perception and cognition — guide every design decision in the ORCA process:

1. **Objects** — Things that are different should look different. *(Anti-pattern: Masked Objects — different objects disguised as the same thing)*
2. **Relationships** — Humans navigate most naturally through relationships between objects. *(Anti-pattern: Isolated Objects — objects with no visible connections)*
3. **CTAs** — Humans act on objects through direct manipulation. *(Anti-pattern: Broken Objects — objects users can see but can't act on directly)*
4. **Attributes** — Objects that are the same should look the same, unless they have a stellar reason not to. *(Anti-pattern: Shapeshifters — the same object looking arbitrarily different across contexts)*

## Available Skills

### Round 1: Discovery — "What's in our system?"

| # | Skill ID | Name | What It Produces |
|---|---|---|---|
| 01 | `01-object-discovery` | Object Discovery | Validated object list (SIP-tested) |
| 02 | `02-nom-builder` | NOM Builder | Nested-Object Matrix |
| 03 | `03-cta-matrix-builder` | CTA Matrix Builder | CTA Matrix |
| 04 | `04-object-map-builder` | Object Map Builder | Object Map diagram |

### Round 2: Prioritization — "What matters most?"

| # | Skill ID | Name | What It Produces |
|---|---|---|---|
| 05 | `05-object-guide-builder` | Object Guide Builder | Prioritized Object Guide (written to `library/objects/`) |
| 06 | `06-mcsfd-spec-writer` | MCSFD Spec Writer | Prioritized relationship specifications |
| 07 | `07-cta-prioritization` | CTA Prioritization | Force-ranked CTAs (P/S/T/Q) |
| 08 | `08-attribute-prioritization` | Attribute Prioritization | Force-ranked attributes + Object Map reorder |

### Round 3: Representation — "How does it look and behave?"

Each step in the Representation round directly addresses one of the Four Ancient Truths and fights a specific anti-pattern:

| # | Skill ID | Name | Ancient Truth | Anti-Pattern Avoided | What It Produces |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| 09 | `09-object-card-designer` | Object Card Designer | Objects | Masked Objects | Visually distinct object cards |
| 10 | `10-nav-flow-designer` | Nav Flow Designer | Relationships | Isolated Objects | Navigation blueprint with nested objects |
| 11 | `11-cta-placement-designer` | CTA Placement Designer | CTAs | Broken Objects | CTA-equipped cards and detail pages |
| 12 | `12-shapeshifter-matrix-builder` | Shapeshifter Matrix Builder | Attributes | Shapeshifters | Intentional object variant matrix |

